    {
      "topic_id": "waves",
      "title": "Waves: Sound, Light & Oscillations",
      "order": 3,
      "explanation": {
        "simple": "A wave is a disturbance that transfers energy from one place to another without transferring matter. There are two types: transverse waves (like light and water waves, where oscillation is perpendicular to wave direction) and longitudinal waves (like sound, where oscillation is parallel to wave direction). Key properties include wavelength, frequency, amplitude, and speed.",
        "advanced": "Waves are described by the wave equation: ∂²y/∂t² = v²(∂²y/∂x²). Solutions include y(x,t) = A sin(kx - ωt + φ), where k = 2π/λ (wave number), ω = 2πf (angular frequency). Superposition yields interference (constructive: Δφ = 2nπ; destructive: Δφ = (2n+1)π). Standing waves form at resonance conditions. The Doppler effect accounts for frequency shifts due to relative source-observer motion. Electromagnetic waves are self-propagating E and B field oscillations (Maxwell's equations), requiring no medium, while mechanical waves (sound) require a medium."
      },
      "formulas": [
        {
          "name": "Wave Speed",
          "latex": "v = f\\lambda",
          "variables": {
            "v": {"description": "Wave speed", "unit": "m/s"},
            "f": {"description": "Frequency", "unit": "Hz"},
            "λ": {"description": "Wavelength", "unit": "m"}
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Period-Frequency Relation",
          "latex": "T = \\frac{1}{f}",
          "variables": {
            "T": {"description": "Period — time for one complete cycle", "unit": "s"}
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Wave Equation",
          "latex": "y(x,t) = A\\sin(kx - \\omega t + \\phi)",
          "variables": {
            "A": {"description": "Amplitude — max displacement", "unit": "m"},
            "k": {"description": "Wave number (k = 2π/λ)", "unit": "rad/m"},
            "ω": {"description": "Angular frequency (ω = 2πf)", "unit": "rad/s"},
            "φ": {"description": "Phase constant", "unit": "rad"}
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Doppler Effect",
          "latex": "f' = f \\cdot \\frac{v \\pm v_o}{v \\mp v_s}",
          "variables": {
            "f'": {"description": "Observed frequency", "unit": "Hz"},
            "v": {"description": "Speed of wave in medium", "unit": "m/s"},
            "v_o": {"description": "Speed of observer", "unit": "m/s"},
            "v_s": {"description": "Speed of source", "unit": "m/s"}
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Intensity",
          "latex": "I \\propto A^2",
          "variables": {
            "I": {"description": "Intensity (energy per unit area per unit time)", "unit": "W/m²"}
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Standing Wave on String",
          "latex": "f_n = \\frac{n}{2L}\\sqrt{\\frac{T}{\\mu}}, \\quad n = 1,2,3,...",
          "variables": {
            "n": {"description": "Harmonic number", "unit": ""},
            "L": {"description": "Length of string", "unit": "m"},
            "T": {"description": "Tension", "unit": "N"},
            "μ": {"description": "Linear mass density", "unit": "kg/m"}
          }
        }
      ],
